{
  "texts": [
    "In few-shot learning models, we provide the limited number of labelled datasets to the model.",
    "We tested 2-way 1-shot and 2-way 5-shot models, which means that there are two labels and one/ five labelled data for each label are granted to the GPT-3.5 models ('textdavinci-003').",
    "The example prompt is given in Fig. 2d.",
    "The 2-way 1-shot models resulted in an accuracy of 95.7%, which indicates that providing just one example for each category has a significant effect on the prediction.",
    "Furthermore, increasing the number of examples (2-way 5-shots models) leads to improved performance, where the accuracy, precision, and recall are 96.1%, 95.0%, and 99.1%."
  ]
}